c_entitlement.Base._part_repr", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "key", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aarc_entitlement.Base.__repr__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Serialize the entitlement to its respective format.\n\nThis is the inverse to `__init__` and thus `ent_str == repr(aarc_entitlement.Base(ent_str))`\nholds for any valid entitlement."]}, {"name": "aarc_entitlement.Base._part_str", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "key", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aarc_entitlement.Base.__str__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aarc_entitlement.Base.__hash__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aarc_entitlement.Base.__le__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "other", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aarc_entitlement.Base.satisfies", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "required", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Check if `self` satisfies the demands of `required`.\n`self` satisfies the requirement if it is equal to or more permissive than `required`.\n\n```\nparam  required\n\nAn entitlement which is required e.g. for using a service.\n\nreturn\n\nTrue, if the requirement is satisfied. Otherwise,  is returned.\n```\n"]}, {"name": "aarc_entitlement.Base.is_contained_in", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "other", "type